HEADWORD: Saltwort
<hw>Salt"wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
name given to several plants which grow on the seashore, as the
<spn>Batis maritima</spn>, and the glasswort. See
<er>Glasswort</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Black saltwort</b></col>, <cd>the sea
milkwort.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salty</ent>⟦br⟧
